Package: ConvRt
Type: Package
Title: Generation-Interval Estimation of the Time-Varying Reproduction Number
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R:
    person("Jeremy", "Goldwasser", email = "jeremy_goldwasser@berkeley.edu",
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A regularized identity-link Poisson estimator of the time-varying
    reproduction number R_t. ConvRt fits a smoothing-spline R_t through the
    renewal equation and predicts the observed counts. The only epidemiological
    inputs are a generation interval and a reporting delay, each a single PMF.
    Provides retrospective and real-time (right-censored, tapered-tail with
    split-conformal intervals) fits, plus weekly-aggregated and trend-filtered
    variants.
